<text>Paragraph alignment, bullet and identation

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

You can change the alignment and spacing of a paragraph in the text. Here are a few examples:

 

This is a right-aligned paragraph.
This is a center-aligned paragraph.
This is a left-aligned paragraph.
   This is a bulleted paragraph.
This is an indented paragrah.
This is a paragraph with 300 pixels left indent and 200 pixels right indent.
This is a paragraph with 50 pixels space above and 50 pixels space below.
 

You can set these with the buttons in the tool bar, or right-click (or CTRL+click on Mac OS X without a multiple-button mouse) on the main window and choose the &quot;Paragraph&quot; item from the pop-up menu, or choose &quot;Option&gt;Paragraph&quot; from the main menu bar. In the latter two cases, you will see the following window:

  
[This is a screenshot. Note: Line spacing, first indent and justified alignment do not work yet.]

To change the bullet icon, right-click (or CTRL+click on Mac OS X without a multiple-button mouse) on the main window and choose the &quot;Bullet&quot; item from the pop-up menu, or choose &quot;Option&gt;Bullet&quot; from the main menu bar. You will see the following window:

  
[This is a screenshot.]

Click one of the inset windows to apply the corresponding bullet icon to the currently selected paragraph(s).

